    "body": "Since we enabled `ruff format` and landed a HUUUUGE PR #1417.\r\n\r\n- #1417\r\n\r\nMost tracked Python files now have trimed tailing whitespaces and ensured a blank line at the end-of-file. I think it's time to enable the pre-commit hook `trailing-whitespace` and `end-of-file-fixer` in the whole codebase not only `.py` files.\n\n<!-- This is an auto-generated comment: release notes by coderabbit.ai -->\n## Summary by CodeRabbit\n\n# Release Notes\n\n* **New Features**\n  * Enhanced pre-commit hooks for improved code quality checks (trailing whitespace detection, executable validation, AST analysis, and debug statement detection)\n\n* **Chores**\n  * Added proper bash shebangs to shell scripts for correct execution\n  * Normalized end-of-file formatting across files\n  * Refined license header application to preserve script shebangs\n  * Various formatting and whitespace cleanup across documentation and configuration files\n\n<sub>✏️ Tip: You can customize this high-level summary in your review settings.</sub>\n<!-- end of auto-generated comment: release notes by coderabbit.ai -->",
